IO a few tacos this week! :taco:
@McKenzi Gooch delivered the final analysis of <http://snow.com|snow.com! It has been SO much fun to watch her unfurl this analysis... so much so that I hope it can be more widely shared soon! :open_hands:
@Amberlyn Etienne &amp; @Sean Miller both received positive feedback  separate Sephora clients this week! Amberlyn for test delivery and Sean for dash construction innovation.  This happens a lot for them both, but it never gets old :upside_down_face:
Must also mention Amberlyn identified opportunities to improve our ways of working on the Vail MEG scope-- Love to see the proactive thinking!! :brainstorm2:
@Astha Saxena thanks for leading an awesome convo in the DABU Managers Meeting yesterday! :speech_balloon:
@Samuel Pratt (with the help of a few others... I'm going to need more tacos!!) is helping resolve an SBSEG Experimentation discrepancy -- thanks for jumping in on this :pooljump:
Thanks, everyone!!! :muscle:

@Raghav Jupally thanks so much for your partnership and hard work pitching Data Enablement work for Vail!  You have so much going on but made this client a top priority which I (and they) very much appreciate.
@Alex Krumins congrats on winning the Concord Core Values award in our BU meeting yesterday-- we're clearly very lucky to have you on Vail (&amp; kudos to @Brock Sauvage for probably the best writeup we've ever seen :mario_wave:).

Outside of Vail...
Additionally want to thank @John Carney for jumping in and helping us attempt to troubleshoot some Sharepoint challenges as we roll out the new training site -- you have so much on your plate already and this was a huge help.
@Krissy Tripp helped resolve urgent client issues the night before work travel &amp; after a pretty long day with separate challenges-- You're always willing to jump in and it's appreciated &amp; recognized more than you know! :star:

