some more cool things happened today...

@John Carney hosted a code review with our team during our practice meeting - really fun collaboration. Loved seeing everyone's wheels turning and solving this problem live over a lunch meeting was a fun change of pace.
It was also a great opportunity to remind everyone that the MOST <https://beautiful-soup-4.readthedocs.io/en/latest/_sources/index.rst.txt|BeautifulSoup in the world is still my dog Chowder :dog::ramen: -- sorry to my team who had to hear this dad python joke earlier today :upside_down_face:)

@McKenzi Gooch & @Gressi Lopez are untangling some webs to get to the bottom of a Vail data discrepancy-- never an easy task, but they're going about this methodically & working together as a team to resolve!! :spider_web::spiderman_pointing:

:taco: (more awesomeness was witnessed, but those are all my tacos for today)

